snippet.textDisplay: The common theme in coke studio this time is about conversation between two people/group where they are either taking comfort  in each others word, or trying to share an alternate view to the other person or jointly just echoing  their internal conflicts. It's about community and finding comfort  in each others word and no matter what your cultural heritage  is the feelings , emotions , thoughts are universal. The pain points , dreams and frustration  and hope all are same.

snippet.textDisplay: The way I have perceived this song, it feels like a person telling and expressing the void he has within, and in those moments, When you yearn to have someone, who can just come and give a pat on your shoulder and tells you everything is going to be just okay. This song is telling just that emotion through this mesmerizing tune. And that humming thing in the end means that Abdul Hannan has also started expecting and sensing hope.
